    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The class defines a callback that <ref refid="classDali_1_1VertexBuffer" kindref="compound">VertexBuffer</ref> object may call to obtain new data. The callback runs before draw call is issued and it will run on update/render thread (developers must synchronize explicitly).</para>
<para><ref refid="classDali_1_1Callback" kindref="compound">Callback</ref> returns number of bytes written. This will limit next draw call to number of elements that have been written by the callback.</para>
<para>Using callback invalidates current vertex buffer data. Unchanged data stays undefined. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
